label: DriveWheelConfigurationValue
comment: A value indicating which roadwheels will receive torque.

enumerationMembers.label: AllWheelDriveConfiguration
enumerationMembers.comment: All-wheel Drive is a transmission layout where the engine drives all four wheels.

enumerationMembers.label: FourWheelDriveConfiguration
enumerationMembers.comment: Four-wheel drive is a transmission layout where the engine primarily drives two wheels with a part-time four-wheel drive capability.

enumerationMembers.label: FrontWheelDriveConfiguration
enumerationMembers.comment: Front-wheel drive is a transmission layout where the engine drives the front wheels.

enumerationMembers.label: RearWheelDriveConfiguration
enumerationMembers.comment: Real-wheel drive is a transmission layout where the engine drives the rear wheels.
